cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DB 

This paper deals with the problem of semantic annotation of microblog topics, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also uses temporal information from Wikipedia edit history and page view logs, which falls under the scope of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also deals with data management and storage, which could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.DB (Databases).
